{sov: V1}
[E]Saint Stephen [D]with a rose, [A]In and out of the [E]garden he goes,
[E]Country garland in the [D]wind and the rain,
[A]Wherever he goes the people all complain.
{eov}

{sot: Lead}
||: E / Dsus2 / | A / E / :||
{eot}

{sov: V2}
[E]Stephen prospered in his [D]time? [A]Well he may and he may decline.
[E]Did it matter, [D]does it now?
[A]Stephen would answer if he only knew how. [E] [B]
{eov}

{sot: Lead}
||: E / Dsus2 / | A / E / :||
{eot}

{sov: V3}
[E]Wishing well with a [D]golden bell, [A]bucket hanging [E]clear to hell,
[E]Hell halfway twixt [D]now and then,
[A]Stephen fill it up and [G]lower down and [A]lower down a[E]gain.
{eov}

{sov: Break}
[E]Lady finger,[D] [A]dipped in moon[E]light,
[D]Writing "What for?" [A]across the [E]morning sky. [D]
[E]Sunlight splatters,[D] [A]dawn with an[E]swer,
[D]Darkness shrugs and [A]bids the day good[E]bye. [D]
[E]Speeding arrow,[D] [A]sharp and nar[E]row,
[D]What a lot of [A]fleeting matters [E]you have spurned. [D]
[E]Several seasons [D]  [A]with their trea[E]sons,
[D]Wrap the babe in [A]scarlet colors, [E]call it your [D]own.
{eov}

