{sov: V5}
Saint Stephen will remain, All he's lost he shall regain,
Seashore washed by the suds and foam, Been here so long, he's got to calling it home.
{eov}

{sov: V6}
[E]Fortune comes a crawlin', calliope woman,
[D]Spinnin' that curious [A]sense of your [E]own.
[E]Can you answer? Yes I [D]can.
But [A]what would be the answer to the [E]answer [D]man?  [E]
{eov}

{sov: WTB}
[B]High green chilly winds and windy vines
In loops around the twisted shafts of lavender,
They're crawling [A]to the [B]sun.
[B]Wonder who will water all the children of the garden
When they sigh about the barren lack of rain
and droop so [A]hungry neath the [B]sky. [A]
[B]Underfoot the ground is patched
With [Abm]arms of [A]ivy wrapped [B]around the manzanita,
Stark and [A]shiny in the [F#m]breeze.
[E]William Tell has [B]stretched his bow
till [Abm]it won't stretch No [A]furthermore
And/[B]or it may re[Abm]quire a change that [F#m]hasn't come be[D]fore.
{eov}


